headline: Middle East Engine Deals Might Change The Case For Investing In General Electric (GE)
summary: Saudia Group has announced a major agreement with GE Aerospace to supply GEnx-1B engines, maintenance, and technical training for its fleet of Boeing 787s, alongside significant new engine deals recently made with flydubai and Emirates for their expanding long-haul operations. These contracts illustrate strong demand for GE's advanced propulsion technology and deepen its international partnerships, particularly in the Middle East, supporting the localization of aerospace expertise.
